{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c395a7d1-0a67-4085-82c1-424ab7ce8625","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest compatibility layer.** That's the breaking change.\n\n- **MSTest.Sdk 3.x** shipped both Microsoft.Testing.Platform **and** the VSTest adapter, so `vstest.console` could still discover tests.\n- **MSTest.Sdk 4.x** ships **only** Microsoft.Testing.Platform. The VSTest adapter is no longer included, which is why `vstest.console` finds zero tests.\n\n### You have two options:\n\n**Option A – Switch your CI to use `dotnet test` (recommended)**\n`dotnet test` works with Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively. Replace `vstest.console` calls with:\n```\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj\n```\n\n**Option B – Re-enable the VSTest adapter**\nAdd this to your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>false</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\nThis tells the SDK to include the legacy VSTest infrastructure so `vstest.console` works again—but you lose the new platform's features.\n\n**Option A** is the recommended path forward.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a2de7128-bfb6-40d4-9004-93d00f6e4d22","outputTokens":286},"id":"1b6a3cd6-e41c-442c-b432-13efc7e45cdd","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:28:42.286Z","parentId":"5ea65b46-2745-4761-b988-1cbf23a1a533"}
